1 (7) "Self-insurer" is an employer who has been authorized under the provisions of this
2 chapter to carry his own liability on his employees covered by this chapter;
3 (8) "Department" means the Department of Workers' Claims administratively attached
4 to the office of the Governor[in the Education and Labor Cabinet];
5 (9) "Commissioner" means the commissioner of the Department of Workers' Claims[
6 under the direction and supervision of the secretary of the Education and Labor
7 Cabinet];
8 (10) "Board" means the Workers' Compensation Board;
9 (11) (a) "Temporary total disability" means the condition of an employee who has not
10 reached maximum medical improvement from an injury and has not reached a
11 level of improvement that would permit a return to employment;
12 (b) "Permanent partial disability" means the condition of an employee who, due
13 to an injury, has a permanent disability rating but retains the ability to work;
14 and
15 (c) "Permanent total disability" means the condition of an employee who, due to
16 an injury, has a permanent disability rating and has a complete and permanent
17 inability to perform any type of work as a result of an injury, except that total
18 disability shall be irrebuttably presumed to exist for an injury that results in:
19 1. Total and permanent loss of sight in both eyes;
20 2. Loss of both feet at or above the ankle;
21 3. Loss of both hands at or above the wrist;
22 4. Loss of one (1) foot at or above the ankle and the loss of one (1) hand at
23 or above the wrist;
24 5. Permanent and complete paralysis of both arms, both legs, or one (1)
25 arm and one (1) leg;
26 6. Incurable insanity or imbecility; or
27 7. Total loss of hearing;
