22 Section 3. KRS 342.120 is amended to read as follows:
23 (1) There is created the Division of Workers' Compensation Funds in the Department
24 of Workers' Claims that[which] shall be responsible for the administration of the
25 special fund and the coal workers' pneumoconiosis fund and the maintenance of
26 records regarding the payment of claims by these funds. The Division of Workers'
27 Compensation Funds shall have no responsibility for the coal workers'
Page 13 of 58
SB034310.100 - 1402 - XXXX 3/10/2026 3:36 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 343/GA
1 pneumoconiosis fund once the assets and liabilities have been transferred to the
2 Kentucky Employers' Mutual Insurance Authority, which will administer the fund
3 pursuant to KRS 342.1243. The Division of Workers' Compensation Funds shall be
4 headed by a director appointed by the commissioner[secretary of the Education and
5 Labor Cabinet], with the prior written approval of the Governor pursuant to KRS
6 12.050. The director shall be responsible for overseeing the administration of the
7 funds and the maintenance of records regarding the payment of claims by the funds.
8 (2) The special fund shall have no liability upon any claim in which the injury
9 occurred, or for cumulative trauma, the disability became manifest, or, for
10 occupational disease, if the date of injury or last exposure occurred, after December
11 12, 1996.
12 (3) Where the employer has settled its liability for income benefits and thereafter a
13 determination has been made of the special fund's liability, the special fund portion
14 of the benefit rate shall be paid over the maximum period provided for by statute
15 for that disability, with the period of payment beginning on the date settlement was
16 approved by an administrative law judge. This provision is remedial and shall apply
17 to all pending and future claims.
