7 Section 5. KRS 342.215 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) The Workers' Compensation Board is hereby created and established. The board
9 shall rule on appeals of decisions rendered by administrative law judges under this
10 chapter. The board shall rule on an appeal of a decision of an administrative law
11 judge no later than sixty (60) days following the date on which the last appeal brief
12 was filed.
13 (2) The Workers' Compensation Board shall consist of three (3) members appointed by
14 the Governor. Each member shall hold no other public office and shall devote his or
15 her full time to the duties of his or her office. Each member shall be exempt from
16 the classified service, and his or her support staff may be exempt from the classified
17 service.
18 (3) Of the members of the board appointed under this section, any member appointed to
19 fill an unexpired term shall immediately assume the office subject to the
20 confirmation by the Senate in accordance with KRS 11.160 for the remainder of the
21 term. Any member not currently pending reappointment by the Senate with a term
22 expiring on or before:
23 (a) December 1, 2025, shall continue serving a term that shall expire on June 1,
24 2026;
25 (b) December 1, 2026, shall continue serving a term that shall expire on June 1,
26 2027; or
27 (c) December 1, 2027, shall continue serving a term that shall expire on June 1,
Page 20 of 58
