1 2028.
2 Thereafter, each term of a board member shall run for four (4) years from the date
3 of expiration of the term for which the member's predecessor was appointed, except
4 that a person appointed to fill a vacancy prior to the expiration of a term shall be
5 appointed for the remainder of the term. The Governor shall not appoint a member
6 of the board to fill the unexpired term of another board member, nor shall the
7 Governor reappoint a member of the board who has been removed from his or her
8 position prior to the expiration of his or her term. The members of the board shall
9 have the qualifications required of appeals court judges, except for residence in a
10 district, and shall receive the same salary and shall be subject to the same standards
11 of conduct. The Governor shall designate a member of the board to serve as
12 chairman. Any vacancy in the chairmanship shall be filled by the Governor. The
13 Governor may at any time remove any member for cause after furnishing the
14 member with a written copy of the charges against him or her and giving the
15 member a public hearing if he or she requests it.
16 (4) A decision concurred in by any two (2) of the three (3) members shall constitute a
17 decision of the board.
18 (5) Members of the Workers' Compensation Board and the administrative law judges
19 shall be members of the Kentucky Employees Retirement System.
20 (6) The Workers' Compensation Board shall be attached to the Department of Workers'
21 Claims[ in the Education and Labor Cabinet].
