2 necessary in the level of the assessments imposed in this chapter;
3 (e) In conjunction with the commissioner[Education and Labor Cabinet], submit
4 to the General Assembly, not later than October 31 of the year prior to each
5 even-numbered-year regular legislative session, a proposed budget for the
6 biennium beginning July 1 following the even-numbered-year regular session
7 of the General Assembly;
8 (f) In conjunction with the commissioner[Education and Labor Cabinet], provide
9 to the Interim Joint Committee on Appropriations and Revenue an annual
10 budget and detailed quarterly financial reports;
11 (g) Conduct periodic audits, independently or in cooperation with the Department
12 of Workers' Claims[Education and Labor Cabinet] or the Department of
13 Revenue, of all entities subject to the assessments imposed in this chapter; and
14 (h) Report monthly to the Committees on Appropriations and Revenue and on
15 Economic Development and Workforce Investment its monthly expenditures
16 of restricted agency funds and the nature of the expenditures.
17 (3) The commission shall have all of the powers necessary or convenient to carry out
18 and effectuate the purposes for which it was established, including, but not limited
19 to, the power:
20 (a) To sue and be sued, complain, or defend, in its name;
21 (b) To elect, appoint, or hire officers, agents, and employees, and define their
22 duties and fix their compensation within the limits of its budget approved by
23 the General Assembly. Notwithstanding any provision of KRS Chapter 18A
24 to the contrary, officers and employees of the funding commission may be
25 exempted from the classified service;
26 (c) To contract for investment counseling, legal, actuarial, auditing, and other
27 professional services in accordance with the provisions relating to personal
Page 56 of 58
SB034310.100 - 1402 - XXXX 3/10/2026 3:36 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 343/GA
1 service contracts contained in KRS Chapter 45A;
2 (d) To appoint, hire, and contract with banks, trust companies, and other entities
3 to serve as depositories and custodians of its investment receipts and other
4 funds;
5 (e) To take any and all other actions consistent with the purposes of the
6 commission and the provisions of this chapter; and
7 (f) To make and promulgate administrative regulations.
8 (4) The Kentucky Workers' Compensation Funding Commission may utilize the
9 investment expertise and advice of the Office of Financial Management within the
10 Finance and Administration Cabinet. The Kentucky Workers' Compensation
11 Funding Commission may procure one (1) or more consulting firms and enter into a
12 personal service contract with such consulting firms to provide investment
13 advisory, investment counseling, or investment management services. The Office of
14 Financial Management shall participate in the selection of any firms for investment
15 services provided, however, the Kentucky Workers' Compensation Funding
16 Commission shall have the right to make the final decision on the selection of any
17 firms. Notwithstanding any provisions of this section to the contrary, all contracts
18 for investment advisory, investment counseling, or investment management
19 services or for the management of assets shall be subject to KRS Chapter 45A. The
20 fees charged by financial institutions for managing the investments of the funds of
21 the funding commission shall be paid from the investment earnings of the funds.
22 (5) The commission shall be attached to the Education and Labor Cabinet for
23 administrative purposes only.
24 Section 18. The Workers' Claims Legal Division within the Office of Legal
25 Services of the Education and Labor Cabinet shall be transferred to the Department of
26 Workers' Claims as the Office of General Counsel.
27 Section 19. Upon the effective date of this Act, all records, files, documents,
Page 57 of 58
SB034310.100 - 1402 - XXXX 3/10/2026 3:36 PM GA

UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS SB 343/GA
1 equipment, staff, supporting budgets, and any and all unexpended funds associated with
2 the activities of the Department of Workers' Claims when it was attached to the
3 Education and Labor Cabinet shall be transferred to the Department of Workers' Claims
4 administratively attached to the Office of the Governor. All administrative regulations,
5 decisions, and actions promulgated, made, or taken by the Department of Workers'
6 Claims prior to the effective date of this Act that have not been repealed or rescinded
7 shall continue in effect on or after the effective date of this Act, unless and until they are
8 amended, repealed, or rescinded by the department after the effective date of this Act.
9 Section 20. Whereas it is critical to the proper management and administration
10 of the reorganized Department of Workers' Claims that consolidation take place as soon
11 as possible, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its passage
12 and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
